GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 723
Short Title: DAC Exemption from State Device Content Ban. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Alexander and Galey (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT EXEMPTING DEPARTMENT OF ADULT CORRECTION'S INVESTIGATIONS
3 FROM STATE DEVICE CONTENT PROHIBITION.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 143-805 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 143-805. Prohibit viewing of pornography on government networks and devices.
7 …
8 (d) Subsections (a) and (b) of this section shall not apply to an official or employee that
9 is engaged in any of the following activities in the course of that official's or employee's official
10 duties:
11 (1) Investigating or prosecuting crimes, offering or participating in law
12 enforcement training, or performing actions related to other law enforcement
13 purposes.
14 (2) Identifying potential security or cybersecurity threats.
15 (3) Protecting human life.
16 (4) Establishing, testing, and maintaining firewalls, protocols, and otherwise
17 implementing this section.
18 (5) Participating in judicial or quasi-judicial proceedings.
19 (6) Conducting or participating in an externally funded research project at one of
20 the constituent institutions of The University of North Carolina.
21 (7) Researching issues related to the drafting or analysis of the laws of this State
22 as necessary to fulfill the requirements of the employee's official duties.
23 (8) Investigating matters involving offenders incarcerated with, or otherwise
24 under the supervision of, the Department of Adult Correction, or matters
25 related to the misuse of devices owned by the Department of Adult Correction.
26 …."
27 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to investigations
28 performed before, on, or after that date.
*S723-v-1*

